00:05:18.580 --> 00:05:21.850 align:middle line:84%
>> When we drink water or
elixirs that contain stones,

00:05:21.850 --> 00:05:24.850 align:middle line:84%
we are ingesting the
essence of the stone.

00:05:24.850 --> 00:05:28.270 align:middle line:84%
That essence includes the
stone's chemical composition,

00:05:28.270 --> 00:05:30.550 align:middle line:90%
color, and crystal structure.

00:05:30.550 --> 00:05:34.540 align:middle line:84%
It also includes its ability to
absorb and refract or reflect

00:05:34.540 --> 00:05:38.620 align:middle line:84%
light, its softness or
hardness, its density.

00:05:38.620 --> 00:05:41.320 align:middle line:84%
All of these aspects of
the essence of the stone

00:05:41.320 --> 00:05:42.370 align:middle line:90%
are important.

00:05:42.370 --> 00:05:44.800 align:middle line:84%
But when we take something
into our own bodies,

00:05:44.800 --> 00:05:47.470 align:middle line:84%
we must be especially
aware of safety.

00:05:47.470 --> 00:05:50.650 align:middle line:84%
Of these factors, chemical
composition and hardness

00:05:50.650 --> 00:05:54.610 align:middle line:84%
are very important when
making stone water or elixirs.

00:05:54.610 --> 00:05:57.880 align:middle line:84%
The standard for identifying
the hardness of a stone

00:05:57.880 --> 00:06:01.600 align:middle line:84%
is called the Mohs scale
which assigns numbers,

00:06:01.600 --> 00:06:03.700 align:middle line:84%
starting with the
softest stone, talc,

00:06:03.700 --> 00:06:07.720 align:middle line:84%
as 1, and ending
with diamond as 10.

00:06:07.720 --> 00:06:10.000 align:middle line:84%
For purposes of
elixirs and waters,

00:06:10.000 --> 00:06:12.010 align:middle line:84%
I become mindful
of chemistry when

00:06:12.010 --> 00:06:16.240 align:middle line:84%
I use any stone with a
hardness of less than 7.5.

00:06:16.240 --> 00:06:20.600 align:middle line:84%
A relatively soft stone can very
slowly dissolve into the water,

00:06:20.600 --> 00:06:23.510 align:middle line:84%
so we really need to know
the stone's chemistry.

00:06:23.510 --> 00:06:26.510 align:middle line:84%
Some soft stones are
completely safe chemically,

00:06:26.510 --> 00:06:27.830 align:middle line:90%
such as calcite.

00:06:27.830 --> 00:06:31.970 align:middle line:84%
It is calcium carbonate,
and it has a hardness of 3.

00:06:31.970 --> 00:06:35.150 align:middle line:84%
Others, for example,
scolecite, contains aluminum,

00:06:35.150 --> 00:06:38.030 align:middle line:84%
and it's given a
hardness of 5.5.

00:06:38.030 --> 00:06:40.850 align:middle line:84%
If we're concerned about
heavy metal toxicity,

00:06:40.850 --> 00:06:43.220 align:middle line:84%
we can place the
scolecite with a quartz

00:06:43.220 --> 00:06:45.650 align:middle line:90%
crystal for at least 24 hours.

00:06:45.650 --> 00:06:48.710 align:middle line:84%
The quartz takes on the
qualities of the scolecite.

00:06:48.710 --> 00:06:50.990 align:middle line:84%
We call this
potentiating the quartz,

00:06:50.990 --> 00:06:53.855 align:middle line:84%
and it's completely safe
to put it into an elixir.

00:06:53.855 --> 00:06:57.030 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

